        <p class="bold red font_21px">TICKETS TO SHAKESPEARE IN THE PARK ARE FREE!​​</p>
        <p> ﻿Free Shakespeare in the Park is one of the most important programs that The Public provides and is at the heart of founder Joe Papp’s vision to create theater for all. In the last 50 years, more than 5 million people have enjoyed performances at the Delacorte Theater in Central Park.</p>
        <p><span class="bold">Free Tickets for Shakespeare in the Park are distributed in a number of ways:</span><br />​The morning of each performance day, lines form for free tickets at the Delacorte Theater in Central Park. Tickets are distributed at 12pm (noon), 2 per person, while supplies last. Be sure to read the <a href="/content/Tickets/InthePark.aspx" class="lowercase">Free Ticket and Line Distribution Policies</a> for more information.​</p>
        <p>Free tickets are also distributed on this website each performance day by random drawing via our Virtual Ticketing system. <a href="/content/Tickets/VirtualTicketing.aspx" class="lowercase">Request tickets here</a>.</p>
        <p>In addition, a limited number of tickets to specific performances will be distributed on special days this summer via free lines throughout the Boroughs of New York City. <a href="/content/Tickets/IntheBoroughs.aspx" class="lowercase">Schedule and more information</a>.</p>
        <p>We are proud to offer special accessible performances for patrons with hearing or vision. <a href="/content/Tickets/AccessiblePerformances.aspx" class="lowercase">Schedule and more information</a>.</p>
